main event: A civilian observer noted a large unknown object with white lights travelling overhead in North Sacramento, California, on November 2, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for 30 seconds,The observer described the object as round and approximately 50 feet wide,It emitted a loud, clear humming sound,The sighting occurred on a clear night with visibility of 5 miles,The preparing officer suggested that the sighting could have been a C-124 landing at nearby McClellan AFB.
sighted object: one round object with white lights
witness description: Mrs., twenty-five years of age, divorced housewife
